name: KLM Asia Boeing 777-200ER Landing and Takeoff at Calgary Airport
description:
Nice to see KLM's 777 again! KLM's service to Calgary this winter is operated by a mix of A330-300s and 787-9s, but with an occasional 777 thrown in. Here's one such visit from their 777, making a windy landing on runway 35R and departing after a 2 hour stay on the ground during golden hour back to Amsterdam. ATC is included!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Airline: KLM Royal Dutch Airlines (KLM/KL)
Aircraft: Boeing 777-206(ER) (B772)
Flight Number: KL677/KL678
Aircraft Name: "Iguazú Falls"
Livery: Asia
Engines: 2x General Electric GE90-94B
Registration: PH-BQI
Route: Amsterdam-Schiphol (AMS) - Calgary (YYC) - Amsterdam-Schiphol (AMS)
Callsign: KLM 677/678 heavy
Runway used: 35R
Date filmed: December 21, 2018
Local time: 1330/1600
